Ivanka Trump, the First Daughter and Assistant to the President, will be visiting Berlin, Germany on April 25th at the invitation of Chancellor Angela Merkel. She will be participating in the W20 Summit and joining a panel discussion with other women leaders on Women's Economic Empowerment and Entrepreneurship. This visit is a result of a roundtable on Vocational Education and Workforce Development that Ivanka hosted with Chancellor Merkel at the White House in March. During her visit, Ivanka will also tour the Siemens Technik Akademie and have discussions with program apprentices. In addition, she will visit the Memorial to the Murdered Jews of Europe in Berlin to commemorate Yom HaShoah. Ivanka will also meet with Embassy staff and their families at the United States Embassy in Berlin. Her schedule includes a gala dinner as well.